com.centurylink.mdw.camel

Class DefaultProcessLaunchHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.centurylink.mdw.listener.ExternalEventHandlerBase
      • com.centurylink.mdw.camel.DefaultProcessLaunchHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProcessLaunchHandler, EventHandler, ExternalEventHandler
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CxfProcessLaunchHandler

    public class DefaultProcessLaunchHandler
extends ExternalEventHandlerBase
implements ProcessLaunchHandler
    Default process launch handler implementation. Can be extended to customize parsing of the request document object, and for extracting process input variables from the request message.

      • handleEventMessage

        public java.lang.String handleEventMessage(java.lang.String message,
                                           java.lang.Object messageObj,
                                           java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> metaInfo)
                                    throws EventHandlerException
        This is for non-Camel style event handlers. It is not used here. Overriding has no effect in the context of a Camel route.
        Specified by:
        handleEventMessage in interface ExternalEventHandler
        Parameters:
        message - message from external system in string format
        messageObj - message from external system in parsed form, such as generic XML bean, JSON object. It is passed in as null if the message cannot be parsed or does not have an object representation (such as USO orders)
        metaInfo - meta information around the request message, such as protocol, reply to address, request id, event name, event id, event instance id, arguments specified for handler, etc. See constants in Listener.java for typical ones
        Throws:
        EventHandlerException
